dataObjects.subject: http://rs.tdwg.org/ontology/voc/SPMInfoItems#GeneralDescription
dataObjects.title: Biology
dataObjects.description: Is territorial over rocky substrate (Ref. 6307).  Usually feeds alone, or in small groups with other species, on the aufwuchs cover on rocks in shallow water (Ref. 6307).Occasionally, however, members band and form feeding schools of several hundred fish which raid the rich algal gardens of other species.  Also feeds on worms, crustaceans, insects and plant matter (Ref. 7020).

dataObjects.subject: http://rs.tdwg.org/ontology/voc/SPMInfoItems#Distribution
dataObjects.description: Africa:  Endemic and widely distributed in Lake Malawi, including offshore islands.

dataObjects.description:
Depth: 1 - 6m.
From 1 to 6 meters.

Habitat: benthopelagic. Is territorial over rocky substrate (Ref. 6307). Usually feeds alone, or in small groups with other species, on the aufwuchs cover on rocks in shallow water (Ref. 6307).Occasionally, however, members band and form feeding schools of several hundred fish which raid the rich algal gardens of other species. Also feeds on worms, crustaceans, insects and plant matter (Ref. 7020).

dataObjects.title: Known prey organisms
dataObjects.description:
Labeotropheus fuelleborni (Pseudotropheus elongatus, P. tropheops, P. minutus, P. auratus, P. fuscus, Labeotropheus fuelleborni, L. trewavasae) preys on:
Aufwuchs

Based on studies in:
Malawi, Lake Nyasa (Lake or pond)

This list may not be complete but is based on published studies.
